Test Name:
Functionality Over Time

Criteria:
The company will continue to maintain the intended functionality of the product over the product's expected life cycle.

Indicators:
Every feature of the product will continue to work for as long as I can reasonably expect; that is, the manufacturer will not 'brick' certain parts of the product during that time frame.
The manufacturer will not cease to support the functionality I come to expect.
Replacement services will exist if the manufacturer ceases to support the functionality.

Procedure Overview:

Readiness Flag:
3